00:13:02,780 --> 00:13:05,883
It was all 100% the whole kill, kill, kill, kill, smash, right?

283
00:13:06,304 --> 00:13:07,405
No Bruce Banner whatsoever.

284
00:13:07,845 --> 00:13:10,727
And in this one, I really wanted to experiment with the idea

285
00:13:10,768 --> 00:13:12,829
that he was primarily Bruce Banner,

286
00:13:12,929 --> 00:13:15,832
and he was struggling to actually keep the Hulk inside.

287
00:13:16,192 --> 00:13:18,154
So this monster that he was keeping inside,

288
00:13:18,214 --> 00:13:20,756
this monster of the Kratos that everybody knew,

289
00:13:21,237 --> 00:13:23,959
was going to be something that he struggled and failed,

290
00:13:24,580 --> 00:13:26,702
because failure is such a huge part of what we do,

291
00:13:27,022 --> 00:13:29,144
that everything in my life just sort of ended up

292
00:13:29,244 --> 00:13:29,944
in this damn game.

293
00:13:31,025 --> 00:13:33,166
And he would struggle throughout all of this.

294
00:13:33,266 --> 00:13:34,867
And something I was really excited about

295
00:13:34,907 --> 00:13:37,308
was this concept of teaching in the narrative,

296
00:13:37,608 --> 00:13:39,529
experiencing the narrative in the play,

297
00:13:39,929 --> 00:13:42,490
so that you were kind of training your son,

298
00:13:43,230 --> 00:13:46,712
you were teaching him about your life, right?

299
00:13:46,872 --> 00:13:48,193
You were teaching him how to be a god,

300
00:13:48,273 --> 00:13:49,413
and he was kind of, in turn,

301
00:13:49,453 --> 00:13:51,374
teaching Kratos how to be a human being,

302
00:13:51,694 --> 00:13:53,315
something he had forgotten so long ago.

303
00:13:54,855 --> 00:13:56,896
And to some degree, we succeeded.

