00:37:07,234 --> 00:37:07,854
and everything like that,

904
00:37:07,874 --> 00:37:09,255
I had to position myself correctly.

905
00:37:09,695 --> 00:37:11,936
So I still had an opportunity to mess it up.

906
00:37:12,116 --> 00:37:14,177
I had many, many, many opportunities

907
00:37:14,197 --> 00:37:14,937
that I could mess it up.

908
00:37:15,497 --> 00:37:17,440
And in a lot of my playthroughs, I would mess it up,

909
00:37:17,460 --> 00:37:20,903
which was the face palm for everybody on the team.

910
00:37:20,943 --> 00:37:22,465
Every time, I'd be like, I think I got it this time.

911
00:37:22,525 --> 00:37:23,366
And I'd play for everybody.

912
00:37:23,406 --> 00:37:25,508
And they'd be like, no, you're rushing this part.

913
00:37:25,528 --> 00:37:26,289
You're not doing that part.

914
00:37:26,309 --> 00:37:27,470
I was like, ah.

915
00:37:28,031 --> 00:37:29,813
It was like the entire team was the director at that point.

916
00:37:29,853 --> 00:37:30,854
And I was just like, take a note.

917
00:37:30,914 --> 00:37:31,655
OK, yeah, that's good.

918
00:37:31,755 --> 00:37:32,415
All right, all right, good.

919
00:37:34,007 --> 00:37:35,948
Very, very stressful, but it was so much work

920
00:37:35,988 --> 00:37:37,288
that I was like, all right, you know,

