00:41:09,395 --> 00:41:11,616
like a box of curtains backstage.

1009
00:41:11,997 --> 00:41:14,739
Had a couple tables and a little bar in there with some water.

1010
00:41:15,039 --> 00:41:15,499
No booze.

1011
00:41:15,920 --> 00:41:16,640
Searched everywhere.

1012
00:41:16,660 --> 00:41:17,061
No booze.

1013
00:41:18,476 --> 00:41:19,396
Which I think was a good thing.

1014
00:41:19,416 --> 00:41:20,877
I probably really would have screwed up

1015
00:41:20,917 --> 00:41:21,658
if there was booze there.

1016
00:41:23,459 --> 00:41:26,021
So we're sitting there for, I guess we had 45 minutes

1017
00:41:26,061 --> 00:41:27,902
before the show was gonna start, the actual show.

1018
00:41:28,483 --> 00:41:29,463
And we're just kind of hanging out

1019
00:41:29,483 --> 00:41:30,924
and I'm going through everything in my head

1020
00:41:30,944 --> 00:41:32,666
and he's trying to keep me calm

1021
00:41:32,706 --> 00:41:34,227
but anybody who tries to keep me calm

1022
00:41:34,267 --> 00:41:35,568
is just making me less calm

1023
00:41:36,028 --> 00:41:38,170
and I'm stressing more and worrying about all the things

1024
00:41:38,190 --> 00:41:39,250
that could potentially go wrong

1025
00:41:39,771 --> 00:41:41,812
when the curtains pop open

1026
00:41:43,113 --> 00:41:45,435
and a Japanese man pokes his head in and looks around.

1027
00:41:46,563 --> 00:41:47,604
And then he just quickly closes it.

1028
00:41:48,525 --> 00:41:50,226
And I'm like, weird.

1029
00:41:51,607 --> 00:41:52,849
It's like, that was weird, right, Kevin?

1030
00:41:52,929 --> 00:41:54,090
And he's like, yeah, that's strange.

1031
00:41:54,410 --> 00:41:56,572
And I'm like, whatever, it's Los Angeles,

1032
00:41:56,612 --> 00:41:57,353
whatever, that's normal.

1033
00:41:59,755 --> 00:42:01,096
So we're sitting there for another couple of minutes,

1034
00:42:01,717 --> 00:42:04,479
and all of a sudden, in extremely dramatic fashion,

1035
00:42:05,200 --> 00:42:06,761
the curtains burst open,

1036
00:42:07,302 --> 00:42:09,463
and this group of people files in.

1037
00:42:09,824 --> 00:42:13,487
And at the back of that group of people is Hideo Kojima.

1038
00:42:15,226 --> 00:42:15,566
Right?

1039
00:42:15,886 --> 00:42:16,867
Bathed in light.

1040
00:42:20,048 --> 00:42:22,089
Fucking Magneto tiles below his feet.

1041
00:42:23,730 --> 00:42:24,030
Right?

1042
00:42:24,850 --> 00:42:26,771
And I was just like, oh, oh, wow.

1043
00:42:26,811 --> 00:42:28,752
And then I suddenly became like five-year-old me.

1044
00:42:28,772 --> 00:42:30,853
I was like, this is great.

1045
00:42:31,534 --> 00:42:33,935
And he does the Hideo Kojima head nod.

1046
00:42:35,956 --> 00:42:37,796
And then I do the whole like, so.

1047
00:42:40,698 --> 00:42:43,039
Then they just walk in, sit down at the other table,

1048
00:42:43,439 --> 00:42:44,640
as they're talking amongst themselves.

1049
00:42:45,372 --> 00:42:46,593
And I was spending like the next five minutes

1050
00:42:46,613 --> 00:42:48,495
trying to think of an opening line, right?

1051
00:42:48,515 --> 00:42:49,775
Like to go over there and be like,

1052
00:42:49,796 --> 00:42:51,036
so you come to E3 often?

1053
00:42:53,738 --> 00:42:56,240
I came up with nothing, but it distracted me away

1054
00:42:56,260 --> 00:42:58,022
from being stressed out and then I realized

1055
00:42:58,042 --> 00:42:59,403
I'm not gonna go over and talk to this guy.

1056
00:43:00,203 --> 00:43:02,265
So I'm just gonna go back into my own little world.

1057
00:43:03,145 --> 00:43:04,927
And about five minutes after that,

1058
00:43:05,687 --> 00:43:08,509
one of the guys stands up, walks over to our table,

1059
00:43:09,430 --> 00:43:14,694
and says, hello, we are going to eat Panda Express.

1060
00:43:22,689 --> 00:43:23,570
It is going to stink.

1061
00:43:26,953 --> 00:43:27,473
We're sorry.

1062
00:43:29,375 --> 00:43:31,136
Then he bowed and walked back to the fucking table.

1063
00:43:38,723 --> 00:43:40,344
Then I really thought it was weird.

1064
00:43:42,086 --> 00:43:44,167
And I actually at that moment contemplated

1065
00:43:44,528 --> 00:43:46,629
whether I was having some fucked up fever dream

1066
00:43:47,650 --> 00:43:49,171
and that I had not yet gotten up.

1067
00:43:51,059 --> 00:43:52,841
Unfortunately, they had called,

1068
00:43:53,241 --> 00:43:55,683
I actually, interestingly, I actually asked Kojima

1069
00:43:55,723 --> 00:43:58,205
if I could tell this story, because I thought,

1070
00:43:58,285 --> 00:43:59,526
oh, I should get permission

1071
00:43:59,786 --> 00:44:01,287
before I can say this publicly.

1072
00:44:01,968 --> 00:44:05,671
And I contacted somebody that I know that works with him

1073
00:44:06,391 --> 00:44:08,413
and asked him about it, and he said, yeah, okay, hold on.

1074
00:44:09,093 --> 00:44:10,835
Then he got back, and he said,

1075
00:44:12,035 --> 00:44:13,837
yeah, Kojima doesn't even remember that.

1076
00:44:16,339 --> 00:44:18,300
And I was like, oh, that's sweet, fantastic.

1077
00:44:18,621 --> 00:44:20,362
I make a hell of an impression, right?

1078
00:44:21,508 --> 00:44:28,514
So, they basically, curtains open again, time to go, right?

1079
00:44:28,734 --> 00:44:30,956
Then it's the heart beating like absolute mad.

1080
00:44:31,036 --> 00:44:32,537
I'm like, oh crap, oh crap, oh crap.

1081
00:44:32,917 --> 00:44:35,119
So Kevin and I get up and they're escorting us back

1082
00:44:35,860 --> 00:44:38,542
to the thing, he powers on my lav mic

1083
00:44:38,582 --> 00:44:39,803
which just reminds me that oh,

1084
00:44:39,843 --> 00:44:41,665
potentially we could have a catastrophic failure.

1085
00:44:41,705 --> 00:44:42,345
That sucks.

1086
00:44:43,146 --> 00:44:44,307
And we're going up the stairs.

1087
00:44:45,007 --> 00:44:47,389
And as we're going up the stairs to the balcony,

1088
00:44:49,025 --> 00:44:50,746
Everything's going to start, right, very soon.

1089
00:44:50,786 --> 00:44:52,268
People are already in the theater.

1090
00:44:52,488 --> 00:44:53,449
The orchestra's all there.

1091
00:44:54,309 --> 00:44:57,432
I realized that I forgot everything about the whole demo.

1092
00:44:58,986 --> 00:45:01,087
And that was a horror story of mine going like,

1093
00:45:01,188 --> 00:45:03,589
oh man, it's like going and taking a test

1094
00:45:03,609 --> 00:45:04,430
and you forget everything.

1095
00:45:04,870 --> 00:45:06,351
But I didn't think that would actually happen.

1096
00:45:06,391 --> 00:45:07,592
And it legitimately happened.

1097
00:45:07,612 --> 00:45:09,073
I was so amped up about this.

1098
00:45:09,093 --> 00:45:10,574
I was so scared about all this

1099
00:45:11,014 --> 00:45:13,676
that I legitimately forgot what I was supposed to do.

1100
00:45:13,696 --> 00:45:14,837
I couldn't remember the first button.

1101
00:45:14,857 --> 00:45:15,637
I couldn't remember the cue

1102
00:45:15,657 --> 00:45:16,678
that I was supposed to come in on.

1103
00:45:16,978 --> 00:45:17,779
And I was like, oh crap.

1104
00:45:17,799 --> 00:45:19,400
And we're sitting down and Kevin's sitting next to me.

1105
00:45:19,860 --> 00:45:21,041
And I'm like, do I tell Kevin

1106
00:45:21,081 --> 00:45:22,201
that I don't remember any of it?

1107
00:45:23,268 --> 00:45:25,470
Because maybe he'll remember the first thing,

1108
00:45:25,510 --> 00:45:26,370
and that'll get me started.

1109
00:45:26,410 --> 00:45:28,591
But if I tell him, that makes it real.

1110
00:45:29,392 --> 00:45:31,333
So if I just keep it inside, then maybe everything

1111
00:45:31,353 --> 00:45:32,273
will be fine, right?

1112
00:45:32,533 --> 00:45:34,534
So I'm just stressing the whole time, like, oh my god,

1113
00:45:34,554 --> 00:45:35,555
oh my god, what's the first thing?

1114
00:45:35,595 --> 00:45:36,355
What's the first thing?

1115
00:45:36,816 --> 00:45:38,677
And I literally can think of almost every game

1116
00:45:38,697 --> 00:45:41,618
that I'd ever played, except what I was supposed

1117
00:45:41,638 --> 00:45:42,539
to be playing at the time.

1118
00:45:43,864 --> 00:45:45,965
And at a certain point in the overture,

1119
00:45:46,786 --> 00:45:49,527
I had been able to see the kind of tablature screen

1120
00:45:49,747 --> 00:45:52,369
that was playing for Baer as he was composing

1121
00:45:52,729 --> 00:45:53,529
or as he was conducting.

1122
00:45:54,910 --> 00:45:56,331
And I was like, oh, it just came back to me.

1123
00:45:56,351 --> 00:45:59,393
Like an image on the screen made me realize like,

1124
00:45:59,493 --> 00:46:01,734
oh, I gotta hit start at that point when it says 110.

1125
00:46:01,874 --> 00:46:03,575
Okay, yeah, I got it.

1126
00:46:03,975 --> 00:46:07,037
And then it kind of just started to slowly fall into place.

1127
00:46:07,862 --> 00:46:10,322
And it turned out, I think several people on the team

1128
00:46:10,362 --> 00:46:11,803
had said that I did pretty good.

1129
00:46:11,823 --> 00:46:12,523
I didn't screw it up.

1130
00:46:12,823 --> 00:46:14,323
I think it was the best I can get.

1131
00:46:14,903 --> 00:46:17,024
That it actually worked out really well.

1132
00:46:17,464 --> 00:46:20,165
And in the end, it actually did work out really well.

1133
00:46:20,425 --> 00:46:22,005
People responded very positively.

1134
00:46:22,085 --> 00:46:25,106
That reveal of Kratos, we were really excited about Kratos

1135
00:46:25,126 --> 00:46:26,786
coming out of the shadows, but I don't think any of us

1136
00:46:26,806 --> 00:46:28,807
had any clue the kind of response

1137
00:46:28,827 --> 00:46:29,527
we were going to get for that.

1138
00:46:29,567 --> 00:46:31,747
So that was super overwhelming and awesome.

1139
00:46:32,628 --> 00:46:35,528
And I think the important thing about all of that

1140
00:46:36,249 --> 00:46:41,360
about the entire thing besides the fact that I hung out with Kojima while he ate Panda Express.

1141
00:46:42,888 --> 00:46:43,548
And he was not kidding.

1142
00:46:43,588 --> 00:46:45,249
It fucking smelled like orange chicken back there

1143
00:46:45,369 --> 00:46:46,249
for like an hour.

1144
00:46:46,649 --> 00:46:47,250
It was crazy.

1145
00:46:48,610 --> 00:46:50,491
Was that throughout all of it,

1146
00:46:51,391 --> 00:46:52,932
all of us, and me especially,

1147
00:46:53,712 --> 00:46:56,193
I was experiencing doubt at every single step of the way.

1148
00:46:57,334 --> 00:47:00,555
It was this sort of imposter syndrome times a thousand,

1149
00:47:00,915 --> 00:47:03,616
this feeling of what I have to say isn't valid,

1150
00:47:03,696 --> 00:47:05,657
what I'm doing isn't all that good.

1151
00:47:06,697 --> 00:47:08,258
And pushing through that,

1152
00:47:08,578 --> 00:47:10,399
breaking through each one of those walls

1153
00:47:10,479 --> 00:47:11,339
kind of led to...

1154
00:47:12,280 --> 00:47:15,243
Well, sadly, another wall of doubt that would be there.

1155
00:47:15,403 --> 00:47:17,585
But that was sort of the process.

1156
00:47:17,745 --> 00:47:19,867
That was the process of pushing through all of that

1157
00:47:20,447 --> 00:47:22,809
and ensuring that we could get to that end result.

1158
00:47:22,830 --> 00:47:23,810
And there was times even.

1159
00:47:25,064 --> 00:47:27,785
right before, in that two week span before E3,

1160
00:47:27,825 --> 00:47:30,907
where we're kind of refining last bits of things

1161
00:47:30,967 --> 00:47:32,427
in the play experience,

1162
00:47:32,948 --> 00:47:34,248
where there was even members of the team,

1163
00:47:34,789 --> 00:47:37,750
very good people, you know, not malicious whatsoever.

1164
00:47:37,810 --> 00:47:40,812
They weren't being mean about it, but they were nervous.

1165
00:47:41,172 --> 00:47:42,253
They were telling me, oh my God,

1166
00:47:42,293 --> 00:47:44,234
I think you're gonna screw up the franchise.

1167
00:47:44,334 --> 00:47:46,555
Like, this is a terrible way to present it.

1168
00:47:46,995 --> 00:47:48,836
One person told me, why don't we have a boss fight

1169
00:47:48,856 --> 00:47:49,216
at the end?

1170
00:47:49,537 --> 00:47:50,718
We should have a big boss fight.

1171
00:47:51,098 --> 00:47:52,339
I think another person even suggested

1172
00:47:52,399 --> 00:47:53,900
we should have Balder on a dragon

1173
00:47:53,960 --> 00:47:55,922
kind of come up when they're at the deer and be like,

1174
00:47:56,002 --> 00:47:57,003
I've been looking for you.

1175
00:47:59,044 --> 00:48:01,767
All these crazy last minute suggestions that I was like,

1176
00:48:01,827 --> 00:48:02,747
oh my god, no.

1177
00:48:02,827 --> 00:48:04,829
And I was basically just saying, don't worry.

1178
00:48:05,970 --> 00:48:08,832
Everything will be fine, even though inside I'm going,

1179
00:48:08,852 --> 00:48:11,034
oh, fuck, oh, fuck, oh, fuck, oh, fuck, oh, fuck, oh, fuck.

1180
00:48:11,795 --> 00:48:15,358
And it's something to remember, I think, for all of us

1181
00:48:15,998 --> 00:48:16,479
in what we do.

1182
00:48:17,518 --> 00:48:20,259
at any time, the next time probably,

1183
00:48:20,319 --> 00:48:21,700
which is five minutes from now,

1184
00:48:22,620 --> 00:48:24,601
you're gonna be hearing that voice in your head,

1185
00:48:25,341 --> 00:48:26,942
or the voices directly around you,

1186
00:48:27,342 --> 00:48:28,822
the people that you work with that say

1187
00:48:28,842 --> 00:48:34,104
that you're wrong, you have nothing good to say,

1188
00:48:35,124 --> 00:48:36,425
you're going in the wrong direction,

1189
00:48:36,805 --> 00:48:40,326
why are we doing this, you suck, you're a jerk,

1190
00:48:40,366 --> 00:48:42,147
well, the last two are just me talking to myself.

1191
00:48:43,547 --> 00:48:43,988
Remember.

1192
00:48:45,150 --> 00:48:47,632
that those voices are wrong.

1193
00:48:49,512 --> 00:48:50,713
And sometimes they're right.

1194
00:48:51,493 --> 00:48:53,494
Because if you remember all the way back at the beginning,

1195
00:48:53,514 --> 00:48:56,736
I was actually right to doubt that crappy demo

1196
00:48:56,796 --> 00:48:58,697
because it was crap.

1197
00:48:59,037 --> 00:49:01,558
And that's the messed up part about doubt in general,

1198
00:49:01,738 --> 00:49:03,999
is that it's right as much as it's wrong.

1199
00:49:04,480 --> 00:49:07,181
And it is up to all of us individually

1200
00:49:07,241 --> 00:49:10,603
for each individual situation to be honest with ourselves,

1201
00:49:11,083 --> 00:49:11,703
to trust.

1202
00:49:12,484 --> 00:49:17,667
ourselves to trust the people around us because they're the ones who really do all the great

1203
00:49:17,727 --> 00:49:24,212
stuff anyway. I just sort of bask in the limelight of their awesomeness. And really endeavor

1204
00:49:24,232 --> 00:49:31,157
to push through every one of those fucking doubt walls because on the other side is always

1205
00:49:31,357 --> 00:49:37,121
something better than where you were at from the beginning. So there you go. That is my

1206
00:49:37,161 --> 00:49:40,604
little chat at GDC. Thank you, everybody.

1207
00:49:44,645 --> 00:49:45,546
How much time do we have?

1208
00:49:45,566 --> 00:49:50,727
Ah, perfect.

1209
00:49:54,488 --> 00:49:54,828
Oh wait.

1210
00:49:57,568 --> 00:49:58,049
Thank you.

1211
00:49:58,389 --> 00:50:00,169
See, I got a slide for thanking you.

1212
00:50:01,369 --> 00:50:04,330
Okay, so we have 10 minutes and we can do questions.

1213
00:50:04,750 --> 00:50:07,211
So, feel free to ask any questions

1214
00:50:07,391 --> 00:50:10,211
except the following two questions.

1215
00:50:11,489 --> 00:50:12,810
What are you working on right now,

1216
00:50:12,891 --> 00:50:14,472
or is there going to be another God of War?

1217
00:50:14,973 --> 00:50:16,154
I can't answer that.

1218
00:50:21,940 --> 00:50:25,183
Two, don't ask who blew the fucking horn.

1219
00:50:27,045 --> 00:50:28,086
Because we're not going to tell you.

1220
00:50:28,366 --> 00:50:29,727
That's like the polar bear in Lost, man.

1221
00:50:29,747 --> 00:50:30,748
I'm not going to say anything about that.

1222
00:50:31,649 --> 00:50:32,110
All right, great.

1223
00:50:32,894 --> 00:50:33,795
Fire away, my friend.

1224
00:50:34,035 --> 00:50:34,856
Hi.

1225
00:50:34,876 --> 00:50:34,916
Hi.

1226
00:50:35,236 --> 00:50:38,318
You talked about a situation with the E3 demo, which

1227
00:50:38,338 --> 00:50:40,580
was great, where you listened to some intuition

1228
00:50:40,600 --> 00:50:42,161
that you had to change it preemptively.

1229
00:50:42,641 --> 00:50:43,642
I was wondering if you could also

1230
00:50:43,682 --> 00:50:46,644
give an example of a time when other people's feedback,

1231
00:50:46,664 --> 00:50:47,965
other people's notes, were actually

1232
00:50:47,985 --> 00:50:49,206
really informative in you changing

1233
00:50:49,226 --> 00:50:50,166
your mind in the process.

1234
00:50:50,667 --> 00:50:53,589
Oh, that's a lot of examples.

1235
00:50:54,590 --> 00:50:55,830
My mind was changed many times.

1236
00:50:55,910 --> 00:50:58,793
OK, there's a really good point in the game

1237
00:51:01,395 --> 00:51:02,916
the son becomes a jerk, right?

1238
00:51:03,616 --> 00:51:06,837
And we had a whole slew of gameplay

1239
00:51:07,157 --> 00:51:09,338
that we needed to build around that.

1240
00:51:09,378 --> 00:51:11,358
So there was about an hour of gameplay where he was a jerk.

1241
00:51:12,139 --> 00:51:14,239
And we had to cut it.

1242
00:51:14,980 --> 00:51:17,440
So there was a point where production-wise, time-wise,

1243
00:51:17,780 --> 00:51:19,461
no more big arms were gonna give me more money,

1244
00:51:20,081 --> 00:51:22,142
that I just had to, I had to get rid of it.

1245
00:51:22,702 --> 00:51:25,923
But that meant that a huge chunk of the story

1246
00:51:26,163 --> 00:51:27,863
was getting cut out, and we needed to figure out

1247
00:51:27,903 --> 00:51:29,064
how to put it back in place.

1248
00:51:29,804 --> 00:51:31,004
And I was like, OK, you know what?

1249
00:51:31,044 --> 00:51:32,825
We're just going to do something really quick.

1250
00:51:32,845 --> 00:51:33,825
We'll do this small piece.

1251
00:51:33,845 --> 00:51:34,865
We'll do a small cinematic.

1252
00:51:35,145 --> 00:51:37,506
Because I had been selling people for so long

1253
00:51:37,546 --> 00:51:41,427
and begging people for so long to put more effort in, do this,

1254
00:51:41,527 --> 00:51:43,487
can add this extra thing, that I figured

1255
00:51:43,547 --> 00:51:45,467
this was the thing that's going to break them

1256
00:51:45,587 --> 00:51:46,768
if I asked them to go too far.

1257
00:51:47,368 --> 00:51:49,848
And the animators, the cinematic group,

